Atmega328 - ATmega328 is commonly used in many projects and autonomous systems where a simple, low-powered, low-cost micro-controller.
LED -  A light-emitting diode (LED) is a semiconductor device that emits light when an electric current flows through it.
Pull-up resistor - Pull-up resistors are frequently used in interfacing devices like interfacing a switch to microcontroller.
Switch - Switch is used to open or close the circuit.
Battery - It consisting of one or more cells, in which chemical energy is converted into electricity and used as a source of power.
Voltmeter - An instrument for measuring electric potential in volts .

